  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Each event with a known seismicity label was subject to a visual review (stick-slip and teleseismic events are available as.pdf products organized by assigned labels in https://github.com/beccalatto/multi_sta_lta/, with documentation for the plotting routine \"MyAnalystPlots\").",
    "Further information on how the labels for stick-slip and teleseismic events were verified by analysts and are also included within a subfolder containing the labeled catalogues and related README text file.",
    "Catalogue users may find that an event is high confidence but not immediately evident in a visual inspection of the time series.",
    "Multiple, successive station triggers add confidence to such events and usually show a change in frequency content on more detailed analysis.",
    "Other events that are attributable to known seismic sources The first event (a) has been identified as a basal stick-slip event by Pratt et al. (2014)."
  ],
